Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async dialog; return true to cancel navigation
            Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            });

            return true; // cancel the default back navigation
        }

        return false; // allow normal navigation
    }
}
```

> `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/OS back button** (Android back gesture, etc.). Return `true` to cancel, `false` to allow.

**2. Custom "Cancel" toolbar button (replaces the shell back arrow):**

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- ... your form ... -->
</ContentPage>
```

Or inline:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                        Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

**3. ViewModel command with confirmation:**

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
private async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` → intercepts the **system** back button.
- `BackButtonBehavior` with `TextOverride="Cancel"` → replaces the **shell nav-bar** back arrow with a "Cancel" text button and routes taps through your command.
- Both paths should share the same confirmation logic.
